Summary: Properties and methods for configuring a 2D light occluder's shape, light mask, and collision behavior.  

OccluderPolygon2D occluder  
Method: set_occluder_polygon(value: OccluderPolygon2D) → void  
Method: get_occluder_polygon() → OccluderPolygon2D  
The OccluderPolygon2D used to compute the shadow.  

int occluder_light_mask = 1  
Method: set_occluder_light_mask(value: int) → void  
Method: get_occluder_light_mask() → int  
The LightOccluder2D's occluder light mask. The LightOccluder2D will cast shadows only from Light2D(s) that have the same light mask(s).  

bool sdf_collision = true  
Method: set_as_sdf_collision(value: bool) → void  
Method: is_set_as_sdf_collision() → bool  
If enabled, the occluder will be part of a real-time generated signed distance field that can be used in custom shaders.